As a result of the work being undertaken, Virgin is "strongly recommending" that passengers do not travel between Good Friday and Easter Monday.
And speaking of the work being carried out at Watford, Network Rail route managing director Martin Frobisher said: "There is never a good time to carry out this type of work but we have liaised closely with the train operators to plan for it to take place at a quieter time on the railway."
On the roads, Highways England - formerly the Highways Agency - said more than 550 miles of roadworks will be lifted over Easter on England's motorways and major A roads.
