Breakdown company Green Flag said 54,000 callouts were expected over the weekend, with one puncture every minute.  It said the M4 was likely to be one of the worst-congested roads.
Some 16 million cars are expected to take to the roads over Easter.
Gatwick Airport will see some 480,000 passengers between Good Friday and Easter Monday - an increase of about 11% on Easter last year.
